article.headline: St. Francis (Pa.) 76, Bryant 61
article.story: LORETTA, Pa. -- Kameron Ritter scored 14 points and Anthony Ervin added 13 to lead St. Francis (Pa.) to a 76-61 win over Bryant on Saturday. Ollie Jackson and Stephon Whyatt each finished with 11 points for the Red Flash (6-21, 5-11 Northeast Conference), who snapped a seven-game losing streak. Jon Taylor had 10 points. Both teams made nine 3-pointers apiece. But St. Francis outscored the Bulldogs 30-18 in the paint, and outrebounded them 37-24. St. Francis shot 51.9 percent (27 of 52) from the floor, holding Bryant to 43.4 percent (23 of 53). The Red Flash went into halftime with a 39-34 lead, and then took their largest lead at 23 points late in the second half. Alex Francis scored 17 points and grabbed eight rebounds for Bryant (2-26, 1-15), which lost its 13 straight. Ben Altit had 14 points and Frankie Dobbs added 11 points and seven assists.
